number of shares represents less than one percent of the number of shares of Common Stock outstanding.
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(1)</font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">Includes
beneficial ownership of shares which each person named in this table has the right to acquire on or before May 14, 2020 pursuant to previously
awarded stock options, RSUs, and performance units that, although scheduled to be paid in shares in more than 60 days, would be paid immediately upon termination of service, as follows:
Mr. Auerbach, 0; Ms. Bernard, 48,341; Ms. Carter Miller, 50,614; Mr. Dan, 24,229; Mr. Gelatt, 53,834; Ms. Helton, 48,341; Mr. Hochschild, 11,996;
Mr. Mills, 7,847; Ms. Nordin, 4,131; Mr. Pickerell, 10,712; Ms. Tallett, 53,272; Mr. Dunbar, 267,663; Mr. Halter, 84,836; Mr. Houston, 783,161;
Ms. Strable-Soethout, 266,223; Mr. Valdés,109,461; and all other executive officers as a group, 495,785.
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(2)</font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">The
information regarding beneficial ownership by The Vanguard Group is based solely on an amended Schedule 13G filed by it with the SEC on
February 10, 2020, which provided information as of December 31, 2019. According to the Schedule 13G, Vanguard has sole voting power with respect to 396,373 shares; shared voting
power with respect to 75,440 shares; sole investment power with respect to 30,786,349 shares; and shared investment power with respect to 446,559 shares.
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(3)</font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">The
information regarding beneficial ownership by BlackRock Inc.is based solely on an amended Schedule 13G filed by it with the SEC on
February 5, 2020, which provided information as of December 31, 2019. According to the Schedule 13G, BlackRock has sole voting power with respect to 20,626,720 shares; shared
voting power with respect to 0 shares; sole investment power with respect to 23,276,309 shares; and shared investment power with respect to 0 shares.
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(4)</font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">The
information regarding beneficial ownership by Nippon Life Insurance Company is based solely on a Schedule 13G filed by it with the SEC on
February 28, 2008, which provided information as of February 21, 2008. According to the Schedule 13G, Nippon Life has sole voting power with respect to 18,137,000 shares; shared
voting power with respect to 0 shares; sole investment power with respect to 18,137,000 shares; and shared investment power with respect to 0 shares.
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(5)</font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">The
information regarding beneficial ownership by Capital Research Global Investors is based solely on a Schedule 13G filed by it with the SEC on
February 13, 2020, which provided information as of December 31, 2019. According to the Schedule 13G, Capital Research Global Investors has sole voting power with respect to
14,274,750 shares; shared voting power with respect to 0 shares; sole investment power with respect to 14,274,750 shares; and shared investment power with respect to 0 shares.
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(6)</font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">Includes
shares owned by Ms. Strable-Soethout's spouse. </font></dd></dl>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">In addition to beneficial ownership of Common Stock, the Company's Directors and Executive Officers also hold different forms of "stock units" that are not
reported in the security ownership table but represent additional financial interests that are subject to the same market risk as Common Stock. These units include shares that may be acquired after
May 14, 2020, pursuant to previously awarded stock options, RSUs, performance share units and nontransferable accounting entry units such as phantom stock units issued pursuant to Company
stock-based compensation and benefit plans. The value of such units is the same as the value of the corresponding number of shares of Common Stock. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">See
"Directors' Compensation" on pages 21-23 for a discussion of the options and RSUs granted to Directors under the Principal Financial Group, Inc. 2014 Directors Stock Plan and the
phantom stock units credited to Directors who participate in the Deferred Compensation Plan for non-employee Directors of Principal Financial Group, Inc. See "Compensation Discussion and
Analysis" beginning on page 33 for a discussion of the performance units credited to officers who defer receipt of awards under a long-term performance plan, the options and RSUs granted under
the 2014 Stock Incentive Plan, and phantom stock units credited to officers that defer salary into an employer stock fund available under the Excess Plan. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">As
of March 1, 2020, the Directors and Executive Officers named in the security ownership table hold a pecuniary interest in the following number of units: Mr. Auerbach, 1,955;
Ms. Bernard, 3,069; Ms. Carter Miller, 3,069; Mr. Dan, 13,320; Dr. Gelatt, 3,069; Ms. Helton, 3,069; Mr. Hochschild, 15,302; Mr. Mills, 9,741;
Ms. Nordin, 3,069; Mr. Pickerell, 3,069; Ms. Tallett, 10,419; Mr. Dunbar, 226,108; Mr. Halter, 167,119; Mr. Houston, 711,766; Ms. Strable-Soethout,
164,967; and Mr. Valdés, 148,374. </font></p>

<!-- ZEQ.=2,SEQ=69,EFW="2241086",CP="PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC.",DN="1",CHK=724922,FOLIO='66',FILE='DISK124:[20ZAD1.20ZAD41801]EE41801A.;10',USER='CHE105231',CD=';1-APR-2020;21:40' -->
<a name="page_ee41801_1_67"> </a>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ee41801_section_16(a)_benefici__ee402023"> </a>
<a name="toc_ee41801_2"> </a></font> <font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


Section 16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance    <br/> </b></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Section 16(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 requires the Company's Directors, Executive Officers and persons who own more than
ten percent of a registered class of the Company's equity securities (Reporting Persons) to file with the SEC and Nasdaq reports of ownership of the Company's securities and changes in ownership.
Reporting Persons required to provide the Company with copies of all Section 16(a) reports they file. Based on a review of the reports provided to the Company or written representations from
Reporting Persons, the Company believes that during the fiscal year ended December 31, 2019, all Section 16(a) reports were filed on a timely basis, except for one report for
Mr. Auerbach. Due to an administrative error, a report prepared on Mr. Auerbach's behalf immediately following his appointment to the board was inadvertently not filed prior to the
filing deadline. </font></p>
<font color="??????" style="display:none;">​</font>

<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a> </font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="eg41801_questions_and_answers_about_the_annual_meeting"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_1"> </a></font> <font color="#7B7C80" size="5"><b>  Questions and Answers About the<br/>  Annual Meeting  <br/> </b></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_can_i_attend_the_annual_meeting_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_2"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How can I attend the Annual Meeting? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
Annual Meeting will be a completely virtual meeting of stockholders, which will be conducted exclusively by webcast. You are entitled to participate in the Annual Meeting only if
you were a stockholder of the Company as of the close of business on March 25, 2020 (the "Record Date"), or if you hold a valid proxy for the Annual Meeting. No physical meeting will be held. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">You
will be able to attend the Annual Meeting online and submit your questions during the meeting by visiting: http://www.meetingcenter.io/210150695. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">To
participate in the Annual Meeting, you will need to review the information included on your Notice, on your proxy card or on the instructions that accompanied your proxy materials. The password for
the meeting is PFG2020. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
online meeting will begin promptly at 9:00 a.m., Central Time. We encourage you to access the online meeting 10-15 minutes prior to the start time leaving ample time for the check in. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
you hold your shares through an intermediary, such as a bank or broker, you must register in advance of the meeting and no later than 5:00 p.m. Eastern Time on Thursday, May 14, 2020.
Please follow the registration instructions as outlined below under "How do I register to attend the Annual Meeting virtually on the internet?" </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_register_to_attend_th__how03000"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_3"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I register to attend the Annual Meeting virtually on the Internet? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
you are a registered shareholder (i.e., you hold your shares through our transfer agent, Computershare), you do not need to register to attend the Annual Meeting virtually
on the Internet. Please follow the instructions on the notice or proxy card that you received. If you cannot locate your notice or proxy card but would like to attend the meeting, you can enter as a
guest. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
you hold your shares through an intermediary, such as a bank or broker, you must register in advance to attend the Annual Meeting virtually on the Internet. Registration will require you to contact
your bank or broker and request a legal proxy which provides proof of your proxy power. Once received, to register to attend the Annual Meeting online by webcast you must submit proof of your proxy
power (legal proxy)
reflecting your ownership of Principal Financial Group, Inc. common stock along with your name and email address to Computershare. Requests for registration must be labeled as "Legal Proxy" and
be received no later than 5:00 p.m., Eastern Time, on May 14, 2020. If you do not have a legal proxy but would like to attend the meeting, you can enter as a guest. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Requests
for registration should be directed to us at the following: </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">By
email: Forward the email from your broker, or attach an image of your legal proxy, to legalproxy@computershare.com. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">By
mail: </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Computershare<br/>
Principal Financial Group, Inc. Legal Proxy<br/>
P.O. Box 43001<br/>
Providence, RI 02940-3001 </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">You
will receive a confirmation of your registration by email. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_why_are_you_holding_a_virtual___why02743"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_4"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Why are you holding a virtual meeting instead of a physical meeting? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Due
to the emerging public health impact of the coronavirus outbreak (i.e., COVID-19) and to support the health and well-being of our shareholders and other stakeholders, we
have decided that this year's annual meeting will be a completely virtual meeting of shareholders, which will be conducted solely online via live webcast. You will be able to participate in the annual
meeting online, vote your shares electronically after following the above directions, and </font></p>
<font color="??????" style="display:none;">​</font>

<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">submit
your questions prior to and during the meeting by visiting: http://www.meetingcenter.io/210150695 and entering the meeting password PFG2020. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_why_didn_t_i_receive_a__eg402337"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_5"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Why didn't I receive a copy of the paper proxy materials? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
SEC rules allow companies to notify shareholders that proxy materials are available on the Internet and to provide access to those materials via the Internet. You may obtain
paper copies of the proxy materials free of charge by following the instructions provided in the notice of Internet availability of proxy materials. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_why_did_i_receive_notice_of_an__why02552"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_6"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Why did I receive notice of and access to this proxy statement? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
Board is soliciting proxies to be voted at the Annual Meeting of shareholders to be held on May 19, 2020, at 9:00 a.m., Central Daylight Savings Time, and at any
adjournment or postponement of the meeting. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b>Due to the emerging public health impact of the coronavirus outbreak (COVID-19) and to support the health and well-being of our
shareholders and other stakeholders, we have decided that this year's Annual Meeting will be a completely virtual meeting of stockholders, which will be conducted solely online via live webcast. You
will be able to attend and participate in the Annual Meeting online, vote your shares electronically and submit your questions prior to and during the meeting by visiting:
http://www.meetingcenter.io/210150695 at the meeting date and time described above. The password for the meeting is PFG2020. There is no physical location for the Annual
Meeting.</b></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">When
the Board asks for your proxy, it must provide you access to proxy materials that contain information required by law. These materials were first made available, or sent to shareholders on
April 6, 2020. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_what_is_a_proxy_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_7"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>What is a proxy? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">It
is your legal designation of another person to vote the stock you own. The other person is called a proxy. When you designate someone as your proxy in a written document, that
document is also called a proxy or a proxy card. Principal has designated three of Company's officers to act as proxies for the 2020 Annual Meeting: Timothy M. Dunbar, President, Principal Global
Asset Management; Deanna D. Strable-Soethout, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer; and Karen E. Shaff, Executive Vice President and Chief Legal Officer. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_what_will_the_sharehol__eg402344"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_8"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>What will the shareholders vote on at the Annual Meeting? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<dl compact="">
<dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> Election of three Directors for three-year terms; </font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> Approval of the
Amended and Restated Principal Financial Group, Inc. Director Stock Plan; </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
</font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> Approval of the Amended and Restated Principal Financial Group, Inc. Employee Stock Purchase Plan; </font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> An advisory vote to approve Named Executive Officer compensation; and </font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> Ratification of the
 appointment of independent auditors. </font></dd></dl>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_will_there_be_any_othe__eg402272"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_9"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Will there be any other items of business on the agenda? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Principal
does not expect any other items of business because the deadline for shareholder proposals and nominations has passed. However, if any other matter should properly come
before the meeting, the people authorized by proxy will vote according to their best judgment. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_who_can_vote_at_the_annual_meeting_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_10"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Who can vote at the Annual Meeting? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Shareholders
as of the close of business on the Record Date (March 25, 2020) can vote at the Annual Meeting. </font></p>

" valign="MIDDLE">

<!-- ZEQ.=2,SEQ=72,EFW="2241086",CP="PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC.",DN="1",CHK=125690,FOLIO='69',FILE='DISK124:[20ZAD1.20ZAD41801]EG41801A.;14',USER='CHE105231',CD=';1-APR-2020;21:59' -->
<a name="page_eg41801_1_70"> </a>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_many_votes_do_i_have_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_11"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How many votes do I have? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">You
will have one vote for every share of Company Common Stock you owned on the Record Date. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_what_constitutes_a_quorum_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_12"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>What constitutes a quorum? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">One
third of the outstanding shares of Common Stock as of the Record Date. On the Record Date, there were 273,388,576 shares of Common Stock outstanding. A quorum must be present, in
person or by proxy, before any action can be taken at the Annual Meeting, except an action to adjourn the meeting. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_many_votes_are_req__eg402379"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_13"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How many votes are required for the approval of each item? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<dl compact="">
<dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> Each nominee for Director will be elected if there are more votes for the nominee than votes against the nominee. Directors are elected by the
majority of votes cast in uncontested Director elections. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> The vote to approve the Amended and Restated Principal Financial Group, Inc. Director Stock Plan will be approved if there are more
votes for the proposal than against the proposal. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> The vote to approve the Amended and Restated Employee Stock Purchase Plan will be approved if there are more votes for the proposal than
against the proposal. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> The advisory vote to approve the Company's Named Executive Officer compensation will be approved if there are more votes for the proposal than
against the proposal. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> The appointment of the independent auditors will be ratified if there are more votes for the proposal than votes against the proposal. </font>
<font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> Abstentions and broker non-votes will be treated as being present at the meeting for determining a quorum but will not be counted as votes for
the proposals. They have no impact on the Director nominees, the advisory vote to approve Named Executive Officer compensation or ratification of independent auditors. </font></dd></dl>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_what_are_broker_non-votes_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_14"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>What are Broker Non-votes? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
your shares are held in a brokerage account, your broker will ask you how you want your shares to be voted. If you give your broker directions, your shares will be voted as you
direct. If you do not give directions, the broker may vote your shares on routine items of business, but not on non-routine items. Proxies that are returned by brokers because they did not receive
directions on how to vote on non-routine items are called "broker non-votes." </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_vote_by_proxy_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_15"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I vote by proxy? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Shareholders
of record may vote by mail, by telephone or through the Internet. Shareholders may vote "for," "against" or "abstain" from voting for each of the Director nominees, the
proposal to approve the Amended and Restated Principal Financial Group, Inc. Director Stock Plan, the proposal to approve the Amended and Restated Principal Financial Group, Inc.
Employee Stock Purchase Plan, the advisory vote to approve Named Executive Officer compensation, and the proposal to ratify the appointment of the independent auditors.  </font></p>
<dl compact="">
<dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> By Mail.</b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">  Sign and date each proxy
or voting instruction card you receive and return it in the prepaid envelope. Sign your name exactly as it appears on the proxy. If you are signing as a representative (for example, as an attorney in
fact, executor, administrator, guardian, trustee or an officer or agent of a corporation or partnership), indicate your name and your title or capacity. If the stock is held in custody for a minor,
the custodian should sign, not the minor. If the stock is held in joint ownership, one owner may sign on behalf of all owners.  </font> <font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> By Telephone.</b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">  Follow the
instructions on the proxy or voting instruction card or the instructions in the email message that notified you of the availability of the proxy materials. If you vote by telephone, do not return your
proxy or voting instruction card.  </font> <font color="#7B7C80" size="2">
<br/><br/></font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> Through the Internet.</b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">  You may
vote online at www.investorvote.com. Follow the instructions provided in the notice of Internet availability of proxy materials or on the proxy or voting instruction card. If you vote through the
Internet, do not return your proxy or voting instruction card. </font></dd></dl>

<!-- ZEQ.=3,SEQ=73,EFW="2241086",CP="PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC.",DN="1",CHK=595590,FOLIO='70',FILE='DISK124:[20ZAD1.20ZAD41801]EG41801A.;14',USER='CHE105231',CD=';1-APR-2020;21:59' -->
<a name="page_eg41801_1_71"> </a>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_vote_shares_that_are_held_by_my_broker_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_16"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I vote shares that are held by my broker? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
you own shares held by a broker, you may direct your broker or other nominee to vote your shares by following the instructions that your broker provides to you. Most brokers offer
voting by mail, telephone and through the Internet. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_vote_in_person_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_17"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I vote in person? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Because
the 2020 Annual Meeting will be entirely virtual by webcast, you will not be able to vote your shares in person. We encourage you to vote in advance of the meeting by mail,
telephone or
through the Internet. In addition, you can vote at the virtual meeting by using the instructions provided above at "How do I register to attend the Annual Meeting virtually on the Internet?" </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_vote_my_share__eg402057"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_18"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I vote my shares held in the Company's 401(k) plan? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
trustees of the plan will vote your shares in accordance with the directions you provide by voting on the voting instruction card or the instructions in the email message that
notified you of the availability of the proxy materials. Shares for which voting instructions are not received are voted in the discretion of the trustees. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b>Voting instructions
must be received by 1:00 a.m. Central Daylight Time on May 15, 2020.</b></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_are_shares_held_in_the_dem__how02680"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_19"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How are shares held in the Demutualization separate account voted? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Principal
became a public company on October 26, 2001, when Principal Mutual Holding Company converted from a mutual insurance holding company to a stock company
("Demutualization") and the initial public offering of shares of the Company's Common Stock was completed. Principal issued Common Stock to Principal Life, and Principal Life allocated this Common
Stock to a separate account that was established to fund policy credits received as Demutualization compensation by certain employee benefit plans that owned group annuity contracts. Although
Principal Life will vote these shares, the plans may give Principal Life voting directions. A plan may give voting directions by following the instructions on the voting instruction card or the
instructions in the message that notified you of the availability of proxy materials. Principal Life will vote the shares as to which it received no direction in the same manner, proportionally, as
the shares in the Demutualization separate account for which it has received directions. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b>Voting instructions must be received by 1:00 a.m. Central Daylight Time on
May 15, 2020.</b></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_vote_my_shares_held_i__how03204"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_20"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I vote my shares held in the Company's Employee stock purchase plan (ESPP)? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
trustees of the plan will vote your shares in accordance with the directions you provide by voting on the voting instruction card or the instructions in the email message that
notified you of the availability of the proxy materials. Shares for which voting instructions are not received are voted in the discretion of the trustees. </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b>Voting instructions
must be received by 1:00 a.m. Central Daylight Time on May 15, 2020</b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_who_counts_the_votes_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_21"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Who counts the votes? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Votes
will be counted by Computershare Trust Company, N.A. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_what_happens_if_i_do_not_vote___wha02746"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_22"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>What happens if I do not vote on an issue when returning my proxy? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
no specific instructions are given, proxies that are signed and returned will be voted as the Board of Directors recommends:</font></p>
<dl compact="">
<dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> "For" the election of all Director nominees; </font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> "For" the approval of
the Amended and Restated Principal Financial Group, Inc. Director Stock Plan; </font></dd><dt style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font></dt><dd style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> "For" the approval of the Amended and Restated Principal Financial
Group, Inc. Employee Stock Purchase Plan; </font></dd></dl>

<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_revoke_my_proxy_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_23"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I revoke my proxy? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
you hold your shares in street name, you must follow the instructions of your broker or bank to revoke your voting instructions. Otherwise, you can revoke your proxy or voting
instructions by voting a new proxy or instruction card or by voting during your participation in the virtual meeting via webcast. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_contact_the_board_"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_24"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I contact the Board? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">You
may contact the Lead Director through the Investor Relations section of the Company's website at www.principal.com, or by writing to: </font></p>
<ul>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">Lead
Director, c/o Chris Littlefield<br/>
Executive Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary<br/>
Principal Financial Group, Inc.<br/>
Des Moines, Iowa 50392-0300 </font></p>
</ul>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">All
emails and letters received will be categorized and processed by the Company's Secretary and then sent to the Company's Lead Director. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_how_do_i_submit_a_shareholder___how03396"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_25"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>How do I submit a shareholder proposal or nominate a director for the 2021 Annual Meeting? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
Company's next annual meeting is scheduled for May 18, 2021. Proposals should be sent to the Company's Secretary. To be included in next year's proxy statement, proposals
must be received by December 9, 2020. In addition, the Company's By-Laws provide that any shareholder wishing to propose any other business at the annual meeting must give Principal written
notice between January 20, 2021 and February 19, 2021. That notice must provide other information as described in the Company's By-Laws, which are on the Company's website,
www.principal.com. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">For
proxy access nominees to be considered at the 2021 annual meeting, the nomination notice must be received by the Office of the Secretary no earlier than the close of business on November 9,
2020, and no later than the close of business on December 9, 2020. Among other things, the notice must include the information and documents described in Section 1.17 of the Company's
By-Laws. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_what_is__householding__"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_26"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>What is "householding?" </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">We
send shareholders of record at the same address one copy of the proxy materials unless we receive instructions from a shareholder requesting receipt of separate copies of these
materials. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">If
you share the same address as other shareholders and would like Principal to send only one copy of future proxy materials, please contact Computershare Trust Company, N.A. at 866-781-1368, or
P.O. Box 43078, Providence, RI 02940-3078. You can also contact Computershare to receive individual copies of all documents. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b> <a name="eg41801_where_can_i_receive_mo__eg402246"> </a>
<a name="toc_eg41801_27"> </a>
</b></font></p> <div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-right:0pt;text-align:left;"> <div style="display:inline-block;*display:inline;zoom:1;box-sizing:border-box;width:100%;"> <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"> <tbody><tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> <td style="font-family:arial;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;padding-top:6pt;border-top:solid #009CCC 1.0pt;"><p style="font-family:arial;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;">
<!-- COMMAND=ADD_ROWSHADECOLOR,"#FFFFFF" -->
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->
<font color="#009CCC" size="2"><b>Where can I receive more information about the Company? </b></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"></font>
</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">We
file reports and other information with the SEC, which are available on the Company's website at www.principal.com and at www.sec.gov. You may also contact the SEC at
1-800-SEC-0330. The Audit, Finance, Human Resources and Nominating and Governance Committee charters, the Company's Corporate Governance Guidelines, and Principal's Code of Business Conduct and Ethics
are also available on the Company's website, www.principal.com. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
Board urges you to vote by using the Internet or telephone or by returning the proxy or </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b>voting instruction card.</b></font></p>

<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a> </font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_appendix_a"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_1"> </a></font> <font color="#7B7C80" size="5"><b>  Appendix A  <br/> </b></font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_principal_financial_gr__ei401997"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_2"> </a></font> <font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><b>  PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC.<br/>  2020 DIRECTORS STOCK PLAN    <br/> </b></font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_article_i._purpose"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_3"> </a></font> <font color="#7B7C80" size="2">ARTICLE I.<br/>  PURPOSE    <br/></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">The
purposes of the "PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC. DIRECTORS STOCK PLAN" (the "Plan") are to enable the Company to attract, retain and motivate the best qualified
non-employee directors and to enhance a long-term aligning of interests between the non-employee directors and stockholders of the Company by granting equity-based awards as provided herein. </font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_article_ii._definitions"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_4"> </a>
<br/></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">ARTICLE II.<br/>  DEFINITIONS    <br/></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">2.1</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Definitions.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    Whenever used herein, the following terms shall have the respective meanings set forth below: </font></p>
<ul>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">1)    "Award"
means an Option, award of Restricted Stock, an award of Restricted Stock Units, or an Other Stock-Based Award. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">2)    "Board"
means the Board of Directors of the Company. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">3)    "Code"
means the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">4)    "Common
Stock" means the common stock of the Company, par value $0.01 per share. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">5)    "Committee"
means the Nominating and Governance Committee of the Board or such other committee of the Board as the Board shall designate from time to time. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">6)    "Company"
means Principal Financial Group, Inc., a Delaware corporation, and any successor thereto. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">7)    "Domestic
Partner" means any person qualifying to be treated as a domestic partner of a Participant under the applicable policies, if any, of the Company. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">8)    "Fair
Market Value" means, on any date, the price of the last trade, regular way, in the Common Stock on such date on the National Association of Securities Dealers Automated
Quotations (NASDAQ)or, if at the relevant time, the Common Stock is not listed to trade on the NASDAQ, on such other recognized quotation system on which the trading prices of the Common Stock are
then quoted (the "applicable exchange"). In the event that (i) there are no Common Stock transactions on the applicable exchange on any relevant date, Fair Market Value for such date shall mean the
closing price on the immediately preceding date on which Common Stock transactions were so reported and (ii) the applicable exchange adopts a trading policy permitting trades after 5 P.M.
Eastern Standard Time ("EST"), Fair Market Value shall mean the last trade, regular way, reported on or before 5 P.M. EST (or such earlier or later time as the Committee may establish from time
to time) . </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">9)    "Family
Member" means, as to a Participant, any (i) child, stepchild, grandchild, parent, stepparent, grandparent, spouse, mother-in-law, father-in-law, son-in-law or daughter-in-law
(including adoptive relationships), or Domestic Partner of such Participant, (ii) trusts for the exclusive benefit of one or more such persons and/or the Participant and (iii) other entity owned
solely by one or more such persons and/or the Participant. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">10)  "Net
Exercised" shall mean the exercise of an Option or any portion thereof by the delivery to the person exercising such Option of the greatest number of whole shares of Common Stock
having a Fair Market Value on the date of exercise not in excess of the difference between the aggregate Fair Market Value of the shares of Common Stock subject to the Option (or the portion of such
Option then being exercised) and the aggregate exercise price for all such shares of Common Stock under the Option (or the portion thereof then being exercised), with any fractional share that would
result from such equation to be payable in cash. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">11)  "Option"
means the right to purchase one share of Common Stock at a stated purchase price on the terms specified in Article V of the Plan. The Options are nonstatutory stock
options not intended to qualify under Section 422 of the Code. </font></p>
</ul>

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=76,EFW="2241086",CP="PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC.",DN="1",CHK=518379,FOLIO='A-1',FILE='DISK124:[20ZAD1.20ZAD41801]EI41801A.;23',USER='CHE105231',CD='31-MAR-2020;22:17' -->
<a name="page_ei41801_1_2"> </a>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<ul>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">12)  "Other
Stock-Based Award" means an award of, or related to, shares of Common Stock other than an Award of Options, Restricted Stock or Restricted Stock Units, as granted by the
Committee in accordance with the provisions of Article VII hereof. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">13)  "Participant"
means a member of the Board who is not an officer or employee of the Company or any entity controlling, controlled by, or under common control with the Company, and is
not the beneficial owner
of a controlling interest in the voting stock of the Company or of any entity that holds a controlling interest in the Company's voting stock. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">14)  "Period
of Restriction" means the period specified by the Committee or established pursuant to the Plan during which a Restricted Stock or Restricted Stock Unit award is subject to
forfeiture. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">15)  "Plan"
means the Principal Financial Group, Inc. 2020 Directors Stock Plan, as set forth herein and as amended from time to time. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">16)  "Prior
Plans" means the Principal Financial Group Inc. Directors Stock Plan and the Principal Financial Group Inc. 2014 Director Stock Plan. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">17)  "Restricted
Stock" means an award of Common Stock made pursuant to Article VI that is forfeitable by the Participant until the completion of a specified period of future
service as a member of the Board and/or until otherwise determined by the Committee or in accordance with the terms of the Plan. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">18)  "Restricted
Stock Unit" means a contractual right awarded pursuant to Article VI that entitles the holder to receive shares of Common Stock (or the value thereof in cash) upon
the completion of a specified period of future service as a member of the Board and/or at such other time or times determined by the Committee or in accordance with the terms of the Plan. </font></p>
</ul>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_article_iii._administration"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_5"> </a>
<br/></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">ARTICLE III.<br/>  ADMINISTRATION    <br/></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">3.1</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Rules, Interpretation and Determinations.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    The Plan shall be administered by the Committee. The Committee shall have full
authority to interpret and administer the Plan, to establish, amend and rescind rules for carrying out the Plan, to construe the respective option agreements and to make all other determinations and
to take all other actions that it deems necessary or advisable for administering the Plan; </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>provided that</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">, no Committee member may participate in any
decision with respect to such member's benefits or entitlements under the Plan, unless such decision applies generally to all non-employee directors. Each determination, interpretation or other action
made or taken by the Committee shall be final and binding for all purposes and upon all persons. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">3.2</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Agents and Expenses.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    The Committee may appoint agents (who may be officers or employees of the Company) to assist in the
administration of the Plan and may grant authority to such persons to execute agreements or other documents on its behalf. The Committee may employ such legal counsel, consultants and agents as it may
deem desirable for the administration of the Plan and may rely upon any opinion received from any such counsel or consultant and any computation received from any such consultant or agent. All
expenses incurred in the administration of the Plan, including, without limitation, for the engagement of any counsel, consultant or agent, shall be paid by the Company. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">3.3</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Maximum Exercise of Discretionary Authority.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    Notwithstanding anything else in the Plan to the contrary, in no event may
the Committee grant Awards pursuant to the exercise of any discretionary authority granted under the Plan (including the right to increase the value of the standard annual award pursuant to
Section 6.1) that would result in the issuance of discretionary Awards to any Participant in any calendar year having a grant date value, as determined in accordance with U.S. generally
accepted accounting principles, greater than (i) in the case of any Participant who is serving as the Chairman of the Board of Directors but who is not an employee of the Company, $500,000 and
(ii) in the case of any of any other Participant, $330,000 (which is equal to two times the value of the standard annual award stated in Section 6.1 (without the exercise of any
discretion by the Committee to increase or decrease such value)). In no event shall the total compensation payable to any Participant, inclusive of cash based retainer and other cash fees exceed
$750,000 (or, in the case of a Participant serving as the Chairman of the Board but who is not an employee, $1,000,000) in the aggregate. </font></p>
<font color="??????" style="display:none;">​</font>

<!-- ZEQ.=2,SEQ=77,EFW="2241086",CP="PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL GROUP, INC.",DN="1",CHK=873061,FOLIO='A-2',FILE='DISK124:[20ZAD1.20ZAD41801]EI41801A.;23',USER='CHE105231',CD='31-MAR-2020;22:17' -->
<a name="page_ei41801_1_3"> </a>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font size="2"><a href="#bi41801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</a></font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_article_iv._shares_issuable"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_6"> </a>
<br/></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">ARTICLE IV.<br/>  SHARES ISSUABLE    <br/></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">4.1</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Number of Shares.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    Subject to Section 4.3 below, unless the shareholders of the Company approve an increase in such
number by a shareholder vote, the maximum number of shares of Common Stock that may be made issuable or distributable under the Plan is 160,000, plus any shares of Common Stock remaining available for
grant under the Prior Plans on the effective date of the Plan. Shares of Common Stock to be issued under the Plan may consist, in whole or in part, of treasury shares or authorized but unissued shares
not reserved for any other purpose. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">4.2</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Canceled, Terminated, or Forfeited Awards.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    Any shares of Common Stock subject to an Award (as determined under
Section 4.1) or any award made or granted under the Prior Plans which for any reason expires without having been exercised, is canceled or terminated or otherwise is settled without the
issuance of any Common Stock shall again be available for grant under the Plan. In applying the immediately preceding sentence, if (i) shares otherwise issuable or issued in respect of, or as part of,
any Award that are withheld to cover taxes shall be treated as having been issued under the Plan and (ii) any Options are Net Exercised, the full number of shares of Common Stock subject to such
Options shall be deemed issued under the Plan. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">4.3</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Adjustment Due to Change in Capitalization.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    In the event of any Common Stock dividend or split, recapitalization
(including, but not limited, to the payment of an extraordinary dividend to the stockholders of the Company), merger, consolidation, combination, spin-off, distribution of assets to stockholders
(other than ordinary cash dividends), exchange of shares, or other similar corporate change, the aggregate number of shares of Common Stock available for grant under Section 4.1 or subject to
outstanding Awards and the respective exercise prices, if any, applicable to outstanding Awards may be appropriately adjusted by the Committee, in its discretion, and the Committee's determination
shall be conclusive. </font></p>
<p align="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><a name="ei41801_article_v._awards_and_terms_of_options"> </a>
<a name="toc_ei41801_7"> </a>
<br/></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">ARTICLE V.<br/>  AWARDS AND TERMS OF OPTIONS    <br/></font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">5.1</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Grants of Options.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    The Committee shall have the power to grant to any Participant or all Participants Options to purchase
such number of shares of Common Stock, and on such terms and conditions, as it shall determine. The Committee may adopt different terms and conditions of each Option, whether granted to different
Participants or the same Participant, and whether or not granted at the same time. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">5.2</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Exercise Price.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    The exercise price for any share of Common Stock subject to an Option shall be not less than the Fair
Market Value on the date such Option is granted. Except in the case of an adjustment effected pursuant Section 4.3 or as otherwise expressly permitted by shareholders, the Committee shall not
(i) lower the exercise price of an Option after it is granted, (ii) cancel an Option when the exercise price exceeds the Fair Market Value of a share of Common Stock in exchange for cash
or another Award, including, without limitation, another Option, or (iii) take any other action with respect to an Option that would be treated as a repricing under the rules and regulations of
the principal U.S. national securities exchange on which the Shares are listed. In no event shall ordinary dividends be payable or credited in respect of any shares subject to any outstanding Option. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">5.3</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Period of Exercisability.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    The Committee shall determine the date or dates at which Options become exercisable. Each Option
shall, if not previously exercised in accordance with the terms of the Plan, in all events expire on the tenth (10<sup>th</sup>) anniversary of the date of the grant thereof. If a Participant shall
cease to provide services to the Company, such Participant or, in the case of death, the Participant's estate or beneficiary, may exercise any Option exercisable by the Participant at the date his or
her service terminated until the earlier of (A) five (5) years from the date the Participant ceased to provide services to the Company and (B) the tenth (10<sup>th</sup>)
anniversary of the date the Option was granted. </font></p>
<p style="font-family:arial;text-align:justify"><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">5.4</font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>    Procedure for Exercise.</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2">    The Committee shall establish procedures governing the exercise of Options. No shares shall be
delivered pursuant to any exercise of any Options unless arrangements satisfactory to the Committee have been made to assure full payment of the exercise price therefor. Without limiting the
generality of the foregoing, payment of the exercise price may be made (i) in cash or its equivalent; (ii) by exchanging shares of Common Stock (which are not the subject of any pledge or other
security interest), subject to such terms and conditions as the Committee shall establish; (iii) by any combination of the foregoing; </font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"><i>provided</i></font><font color="#7B7C80" size="2"> that the
combined value of all cash and cash equivalents paid and the Fair Market Value of any such Common Stock tendered to the Company, valued as of the date of such tender, is at least equal to such
exercise price; or (iv) in accordance with any other procedure or arrangement approved by the Committee, except that, in no event shall the Company loan a Participant funds or otherwise extend credit
to a Participant to facilitate such Participant's exercise of any of his or </font></p>
<font color="??????" style="display:none;">​</font>
<div style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;">
<div style="display:none;
